[normal]Gas heat pumps[bold] (GHP) 
[normal]can readily address the needs of the retrofit environment and achieve rapid efficiency and decarbonisation gains without infrastructure changes or loss 
[normal]of comfort
[normal] see paragraph 12 and 13 for more information
[normal]. 
[normal]GHPs are a heating technology that can readily contribute to the attainment of binding renewable targets
[normal] but
[normal] RHI support on par with other renewable heating technologies, is essential to provide the 
[normal]necessary incentive, exposure and certainty to start the GHP market in the UK. RHI support would allow GHPs to achieve the strategic potential foreseen in DECC’s Heat Strategy and enable prompt decarbonisation and renewable gains even in case gas utilisati
[normal]on persists.
